Whisk water, white vinegar, and sugar together in a bowl until sugar has dissolved. Stir cucumber and onion into the vinegar mixture; cover and refrigerate for 3 hours. Drain vegetables. Toss romaine lettuce and arugula with olive oil and balsamic vinegar in a large bowl. Season with salt and black pepper. Divide salad on 2 plates and scatter cucumber mixture and grapes on top to serve.